Adeniyi Olugbemi, Sokoto Sterling Bank, as part of its corporate social responsibility, has donated overall uniforms to the Sokoto State Government, for the use of sanitation workers in the state. According to the bank’s management, the uniforms will give the sanitation workers under Sokoto Environmental Protection Agency an identity as well as, enhance their performance. The over 1,000 overall uniforms were presented to the state Commissioner for Environment,   Sagir Bafarawa, by the duo of Ibrahim Aliero and Ado Shehu, Sterling Bank Branch Manager, Institutional Banking and Branch Manager respectively. Aliero said, “The essence of the presentation is to complement the state government’s efforts towards maintaining a clean environment. “At Sterling Bank, we are concerned about our business environment. The overall sanitation kits donated to SEPA is part of our bank’s corporate social responsibility idea to sustain clean environment, more so, when we believe that a  clean environment depicts a good business environment. “These overall kits are durable and of good quality that will endure the weather for a long time.” In appreciation,  Bafarawa commended the Sterling Bank for  its significant corporate social responsibility role. The commissioner also called on other stakeholders to emulate the good gesture of the bank in the state government’s efforts to keep the state clean. Copyright PUNCH.
